docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump awarded the Medal of Freedom to the former N.B.A. great Jerry West on Thursday, the second time in two weeks that the president has honored a long-retired standout from a league whose current generation of stars is known for refusing to visit his White House.

headline.main: For Second Time in 2 Weeks, Trump Awards Medal of Freedom to an Ex-N.B.A. Star

docs.abstract: With the clock ticking toward a potential debt default, federal budget negotiators are maneuvering to isolate the man seen as the common enemy: Mick Mulvaney.
docs.snippet: With the clock ticking toward a potential debt default, federal budget negotiators are maneuvering to isolate the man seen as the common enemy: Mick Mulvaney.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — As the federal government inches closer toward a potentially disastrous default on its debts, lawmakers and some Trump administration officials desperate for a budget deal have carefully maneuvered negotiations away from the man who has emerged as the common enemy: Mick Mulvaney, the acting White House chief of staff.

headline.main: As Washington Seeks Budget Deal, Negotiators Try to Sideline Mulvaney
headline.print_headline: Accord, Not on Budget, but on Who Is ‘Not Helpful’

docs.lead_paragraph: Nationwide raids to arrest thousands of members of undocumented families have been scheduled to begin Sunday, according to two current and one former homeland security officials, moving forward with a rapidly changing operation, the final details of which remain in flux. The operation, backed by President Trump, had been postponed, partly because of resistance among officials at his own immigration agency.

headline.main: Thousands Are Targeted as ICE Prepares to Raid Undocumented Migrant Families
